# Copy to configs/brain.env (gitignored) on each brain machine (main PC and/or laptop).
# Same repo, same file layout — only PI_WS_URL / paths need to match your network.

# WebSocket URL for pi_runtime on the Raspberry Pi (must match pi_runtime port, default 8765).
#
# Prefer mDNS when Pi and PC are on the same LAN — survives DHCP IP changes:
#   On the Pi: run `hostname` (e.g. NicoPi) → use lowercase: ws://nicopi.local:8765
# Raspberry Pi OS ships Avahi; .local names work from macOS/Linux easily. On Windows 10/11,
# .local often works; if not, install "Bonjour Print Services" or use a router DHCP reservation + IP.
#
# PI_WS_URL=ws://nicopi.local:8765
PI_WS_URL=ws://192.168.1.50:8765

# Examples:
# PI_WS_URL=ws://raspberrypi.local:8765
# PI_WS_URL=ws://glados-pi.local:8765
# PI_WS_URL=ws://192.168.1.50:8765

# Optional: override if Ollama is not on localhost (advanced).
# OLLAMA_HOST=http://127.0.0.1:11434

# Match upstream glados_config / brain_runtime default (3B). On a weak Pi running Ollama locally, use llama3.2:1b.
# OLLAMA_MODEL=llama3.2

# brain_runtime only: sliding window of past user/assistant turns (default 24 messages).
# OLLAMA_CHAT_HISTORY_MAX=24
# OLLAMA_NUM_CTX=8192
